			<ns0:name>esei...@chromium.org</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/101644972956654258238/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">It looks like the instructions on code.google.com are wrong.

The correct instructions are:
1.  Install depot_tools (and put it in your path).
2. Make a directory for your checkout.
3.  Put a .gclient file containing:
solutions = [
  { "name"        : "native_client",
    "url"         : "http://src.chromium.org/native_client/trunk/src/native_client",
  },
]
in your new directory.
4.  gclient sync

For whatever reason syncing that way will cause the directories to be set up as the ./scons script expects instead of how they set up if you check out from svn manually.</ns0:content><ns0:updated>2010-11-11T02:11:09.000Z</ns0:updated><ns0:published>2010-11-11T02:11:09.000Z</ns0:published><ns2:updates /><ns0:title>Comment 6 by esei...@chromium.org</ns0:title><ns0:link href="http://code.google.com/p/nativeclient/issues/detail?id=1156#c6" rel="alternate" type="text/html" /><ns0:link href="https://code.google.com/feeds/issues/p/nativeclient/issues/1156/comments/full/6" rel="self" type="application/atom+xml" /></ns0:entry>